{
  "stem": "11174.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then this was almost every day-- except on Friday I don't remember-- this was every day in, in the summer.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Almost every day in the summer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this took a few hours doing this, quite a few hours during the day.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then for Shabbos there was always some, some poor people that-- better-- better class of poor people who went around, they have to-- there was always Shabbos, almost always, I mean, especially in the summer.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Even the winter too.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "These class went already didn't go where they went with-- with their wagon that they paid for it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Usually it was the mail wagon that came.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Shabbos there were always-- there were a few people who took some of the poor people on Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But the first thing was the rabbi's house, so she had to cook up a little more.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There was always one or two even three people with Shabbos table.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And this wasn't only us, but the rabbi was the first one and the most-- it always went to the rabbi's house.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By the way, you're talking about the news, the important news.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Those people were the biggest news carriers, those poor people, [LAUGHS] because they went from town to town.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I'm talking about the news in different communities and different towns.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You became a, a sort of a-- know a-- knowing a lot if you mingle around with people, always talk to them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They love to talk.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I'm talking about those better class who came to the beis madresh.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they-- from every community you had reports with names, you know, different news, you know?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This is not yet-- very interest-- is not yet, I read here and there some books, the people who wrote that shtetl, about the shtetl.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
